        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Harden YouTube transcript view metrics",
        "body": "## Context\n\nFollow-up to #262, which was merged prematurely on June 11, 2026 at `61c793c7` with a failed test check. This PR preserves the shipped CLI/output contract while correcting and hardening YouTube view-count collection, freshness, fallback, and cache behavior.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Validate and merge YouTube view metrics across embedded player data, the player API, watch-page metadata, and yt-dlp fallbacks.\n- Preserve a known view count when a later fallback supplies duration only or observes an unavailable count.\n- Keep hidden/unavailable counts explicit as `null` in JSON and `YouTube views: unavailable` in human output.\n- Reuse fresh metrics for one hour, including stable `observedAt`, while refreshing stale or incomplete observations within the existing best-effort timeout.\n- Verify embedded YouTube transcript-cache identity using the stored resource key, preventing stale transcripts after an embed changes without discarding valid legacy cache entries.\n- Add the repository rule requiring stable dependency releases to age seven days before adoption; prereleases remain excluded unless already adopted.\n\nNetwork behavior remains YouTube-specific and best-effort. Cached observations avoid repeat metadata requests; failures do not block transcript extraction.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm -s check`: 438 files passed, 28 skipped; 2,349 tests passed, 42 skipped.\n- `pnpm -s build`: passed.\n- CI pack assertions: root CLI, core ESM entrypoints, prompts, ffmpeg/ffprobe WASM, and LGPL artifact all present.\n- `$autoreview`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Built `dist/cli.js`, public `dQw4w9WgXcQ`: `1,781,897,219` views, exactly matching yt-dlp at observation time.\n- Repeated public extraction preserved the same count and `observedAt`, proving fresh-cache reuse.\n- Built `dist/cli.js`, unavailable/private `wBwJ7ETeRdE`: JSON `viewCount: null`; human output `YouTube views: unavailable`.\n\nSource contracts checked against the [YouTube videos API](https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/docs/videos), [YouTube API revision history](https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/revision_history), and [yt-dlp](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp).\n",
